        "title": "ðŸ“š Nouns",
        "content": {
          "introduction": "The good news about nouns in Dholuo: there is no gender (like la mesa and el dia in Spanish), and there are no articles (like 'the', 'a', 'an'); the noun stands alone. But nouns can be tricky for a couple of reasons: the formation of the plural is very irregular, and a special noun construct form must be used in some cases. For now, let's look at some nouns and their plurals."
          }
        },
